      • getFrequencies

        public float[] getFrequencies​()
        Array describing the frequency for the different FFT bins. Note that these still need to be multiplied with your sampling frequency to get actual Hz values. Also note, that values beyond N/2 (Nyquist frequency) are typically not useful.

        The returned array is a clone, you may do with it whatever you want.

        Returns:
        array with frequencies for the FFT (bins == index)

      • getFrequencyForBin

        public float getFrequencyForBin​(int bin)
        Frequency for a given fourier transform bin. Note that the returned frequencies need to be multiplied with your sampling frequency to get actual Hz values. Also note, that values beyond N/2 (Nyquist frequency) are typically not useful.
        Parameters:
        bin - bin
        Returns:
        frequency
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given bin number is invalid for this FFT instance
